R

RandomClustering - Class in cs691.assignment04
This class performs a "random" partition clustering of the data to provide some basic sanity-checking values for the other methods you will need to implement as part of this assignment.
RandomClustering(int) - Constructor for class cs691.assignment04.RandomClustering
Create a new random clustering procedure which will "find" numClusters number of clusters (or fewer if there are not enough data points given to the algorithm).
randomProjectionsSeed - Variable in class cs691.assignment04.ClusterEnsemble
The seed value for the random projections (set to ensure experimental repeatability)
removeClassLabel(Instances) - Static method in class cs691.assignment04.Utils
Create a new Instances object that is identical to data except the class attribute (if it exists in data) has been removed from the returned object.
RPEnsembleDistanceFunction - Class in cs691.assignment04
This class implements Weka's DistanceFunction interface in order to use the similarity values calculated during the repetitions of the Random Projection (RP)+EM runs directly with Weka's HierarchicalClustering algorithm instead of having to implement your own HierarchicalClustering algorithm.
RPEnsembleDistanceFunction(Instances, PairwiseStorage) - Constructor for class cs691.assignment04.RPEnsembleDistanceFunction
Create the distance function object to be used in the HierarchicalClusterer.
